.TH "tty_line_name" 9 "tty_line_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_line_name \- generate name for a tty
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" tty_line_name
.BI "(struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "int index "  ","
.BI "char *p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
the tty driver in use
.IP "index" 12
the minor number
.IP "p" 12
output buffer of at least 7 bytes

Generate a name from a driver reference and write it to the output
buffer.

Locking: None
